  "title": "Shrubs - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_828672\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_7008603_828672\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481828\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_7008603_481828\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Shrubs</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008609\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Apache-Plume-Banner.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Whispy and feathery seeds point upward with scattered small five petaled flower and green pointy leaves.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Apache-Plume-Banner.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Detailed flowers, leaves, and seeds on an apache plume. </figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2>Common Shrubs at Grand Canyon</h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008611\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008611\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Fernbush-NPS-Photo-E-Gelfat-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Reddish brown woody stems point vertically with clusters of leaves that appear like small ferns.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Fernbush-NPS-Photo-E-Gelfat-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Fernbush<br/>Chamaebatiaria millefolium – Rosaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / E. Gelfat</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Fernbush</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{108}\" paraid=\"1135544106\"><em>Chamaebatiaria millefolium</em> – Rosaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{114}\" paraid=\"468979240\">Easily identified by its fern-shaped leaves, which are 1-4 inches long </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{133}\" paraid=\"1721174755\">Only woody shrub in the area to have leaves of this shape and size </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{142}\" paraid=\"2103227264\">3-10 feet tall and densely branched </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{153}\" paraid=\"1039230217\">Unique foliage and attractive, cone-shaped array of flowers make it suitable as an ornamental plant in landscaping </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{164}\" paraid=\"1391552023\">Serves as a host plant for the spring azure butterfly </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{173}\" paraid=\"1834475954\">Leaves are covered in sticky glands that produce a pleasant aroma </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008614\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008614\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Rubber-Rabbit-Brush-05-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Narrow yellow flowers point upward out of mint green stalks.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Rubber-Rabbit-Brush-05-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Rubber Rabbitbrush\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Rubber Rabbitbrush<br/>Ericameria nauseosa – Asteraceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / E. Gelfat</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Rubber Rabbitbrush</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{198}\" paraid=\"1356251984\"><em>Ericameria nauseosa</em> – Asteraceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{204}\" paraid=\"407738259\">Large, bushy shrub with foliage ranging from green to gray </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{213}\" paraid=\"70195549\">Somewhat broom-shaped with many stems and small leaves </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{220}\" paraid=\"1846830509\">Numerous yellow flowers in late summer to early fall </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{229}\" paraid=\"438427294\">Fire adapted species that sprouts vigorously after wildfire </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{236}\" paraid=\"1609071209\">Hardy plant that can be used in landscaping or for windbreaks </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{ffda4d3e-366f-4779-891d-a79765718be4}{243}\" paraid=\"783549203\">Contains latex that could be used in rubber production </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008615\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008615\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Wax-Current-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Multi lobed small leaves cluster together on red-brown branches.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Wax-Current-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Wax Current<br/>Ribes cereum – Grossulariaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / E. Gelfat</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Wax Current</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{1}\" paraid=\"295345962\"><em>Ribes cereum</em> – Grossulariaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{7}\" paraid=\"1832218716\">Large shrub, up to 6 feet tall </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{14}\" paraid=\"1704718023\">Leaves are roughly oval with shallow lobes and a sticky surface </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{21}\" paraid=\"53518856\">Produces a pleasant spicey aroma which can sometimes be smelled from several yards away  </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{32}\" paraid=\"1344578724\">Has small tube-shaped flowers that are white to pink </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{39}\" paraid=\"1825654396\">Produces edible red or orange berries (currents) </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008616\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008616\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Big-Sagebrush-400_1.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Lengthy mint green leaves lobed on the top point in the same direction off of a grey branch.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Big-Sagebrush-400_1.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Big Sagebrush<br/>Artemisia tridentata – Asteraceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / E. Gelfat</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Big Sagebrush</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{54}\" paraid=\"1728572885\"><em>Artemisia tridentata</em> – Asteraceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{60}\" paraid=\"919873702\">Large woody shrub (1-9 feet tall) with thick, gnarled trunks </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{75}\" paraid=\"178040025\">Small Blue-gray leaves with three distinct lobes </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{88}\" paraid=\"1573872955\">Strong sage aroma </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{95}\" paraid=\"960497138\">Drought tolerant plant that often occurs in dry basins or plateaus </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{102}\" paraid=\"347550719\">Not well adapted wildfire </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{109}\" paraid=\"1245701762\">Threatened by invasive cheatgrass, which increases the risk of wildfires </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{118}\" paraid=\"674446291\">Food source for wildlife such as pronghorn, sage grouse, and rabbits </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008617\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008617\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Mountain-Mahogany-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Oval leaves, dark green on top and light green blow curve upward, while a few fuzzy feather-like seeds burst from the top of the plant.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Mountain-Mahogany-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Mountain Mahogany<br/>Cercocarpus ledifolius – Rosaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / E. Gelfat</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Mountain Mahogany</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{131}\" paraid=\"182870604\"><em>Cercocarpus ledifolius</em> – Rosaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{139}\" paraid=\"1985341121\">Large shrub / small tree, up to 25 feet tall </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{150}\" paraid=\"77321117\">Has small, stiff, evergreen leaves shaped like elongated ovals </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{159}\" paraid=\"283431934\">Long-lived species, up to 1300 years </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{166}\" paraid=\"80728778\">Seeds have a long white feather-like tufts that aid in wind dispersal </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{173}\" paraid=\"162599626\">Fixes its own nitrogen (essential nutrient) from the atmosphere, unlike most plants </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{180}\" paraid=\"685992218\">Can grow abundantly after fires and form dense thickets </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008618\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008618\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Cliffrose-02-blooming-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Bright green waxy colored leaves are clumped together while yellow five petaled flowers with yellow centers radiate.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Cliffrose-02-blooming-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Cliffrose<br/>Purshia stansburyana – Rosaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / Ty Karlovetz</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Cliffrose</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{193}\" paraid=\"1571069565\"><em>Purshia stansburyana</em> – Rosaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{201}\" paraid=\"339674221\">Shrub or small tree 2-12 feet tall</li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{212}\" paraid=\"1998716753\">Older individuals have shaggy, fibrous bark</li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{223}\" paraid=\"989642425\">Small three-lobed leaves are thick and sticky with a distinctive odor</li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{230}\" paraid=\"178458229\">Seeds have long feather-shaped white tufts. Often, these tufts form small clusters</li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{239}\" paraid=\"850213223\">Has showy white and yellow flowers which can be quite prolific</li>\n<li paraeid=\"{972e718a-849e-4656-a508-43dab57326ac}{250}\" paraid=\"1347136944\">Food source for elk, deer, pronghorn, and domestic livestock</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008619\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008619\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Apache-Plume-NPS-Photo-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Two five petaled white flowers with yellow centers are surrounded by whispy pink feather-like seeds.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Apache-Plume-NPS-Photo-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Apache Plume<br/>Fallugia paradoxa – Rosaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / Michael Quinn</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Apache Plume</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{12}\" paraid=\"2039671390\"><em>Fallugia paradoxa</em> – Rosaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{20}\" paraid=\"914243196\">Bushy, many-branched shrub up to 6 feet tall </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{27}\" paraid=\"635894737\">Has attractive white flowers throughout the summer </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{34}\" paraid=\"1182524385\">Seeds are produce in clusters and have long white feather-like tufts </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{41}\" paraid=\"1466145914\">Similar in appearance to cliffrose, but can be distinguished by: </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{48}\" paraid=\"1532598624\">More bushy, less tree-like form </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{55}\" paraid=\"610185322\">More seeds per cluster, producing a dense fluffy tuft </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{62}\" paraid=\"483091087\">Thinner, lighter-colored leaves which lack a sticky coating </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7008620\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7008620\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Fremont-Barberry-02-flowers-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Pointy blue green leaves branch off of a woody branch with small yellow 6 petal flowers.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/Fremont-Barberry-02-flowers-400.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Fremont Barberry<br/>Mahonia fremontii – Berberidaceae <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / Ty Karlovetz</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Fremont Barberry</h3>\n<p><i></i></p>\n<p paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{75}\" paraid=\"538635793\"><em>Mahonia fremontii</em> – Berberidaceae</p>\n<ul>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{83}\" paraid=\"692793725\">Large bushy shrub: 3-14 feet tall </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{90}\" paraid=\"1725409955\">Easily distinguished by sharp teeth on the margins of the leaves </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{99}\" paraid=\"1654853041\">Produces abundant yellow flowers in the spring </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{106}\" paraid=\"390583691\">Has yellow, red, or dark blue berries in late summer </li>\n<li paraeid=\"{1c7b68e6-1c05-4c81-8999-6f0d1b3efb6c}{113}\" paraid=\"68788046\">Berries are edible, but not particularly palatable </li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: October 20, 2021</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
  "scraped_at": "2026-04-06T13:54:28Z"
}